drm/rockchip: expose a render node (DRIVER_RENDER)

Mainline's rockchip-drm is display-only; the GPU render node comes from panthor.
When the proprietary Mali "kbase" stack is used instead of panthor (kbase owns
the GPU, panthor is blacklisted), there is no render node at all, so Mesa/zink
(e.g. XWayland's glamor) has no GBM/winsys device and fails with
"Failed to make EGL context current with GL".

The Rockchip vendor kernel ships rockchip-drm with DRIVER_RENDER for exactly
this reason. The current libmali userspace allocates buffers via dma-heap (not
the vendor ROCKCHIP_GEM_CREATE ioctl), so only the render node itself is needed:
clients allocate via Vulkan/dma-heap and use the node for the device handle and
dma-buf PRIME, which rockchip-drm already supports. Just advertise DRIVER_RENDER.

Carried by mali-dkms (Rockchip Mali-Valhall DKMS). Not for upstream.
---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/rockchip_drm_drv.c	2026-06-28 20:15:19.206490294 +0100
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/rockchip_drm_drv.c	2026-06-28 20:15:19.243163823 +0100
@@ -231,7 +231,7 @@
 DEFINE_DRM_GEM_FOPS(rockchip_drm_driver_fops);
 
 static const struct drm_driver rockchip_drm_driver = {
-	.driver_features	= DRIVER_MODESET | DRIVER_GEM | DRIVER_ATOMIC,
+	.driver_features	= DRIVER_MODESET | DRIVER_GEM | DRIVER_ATOMIC | DRIVER_RENDER,
 	.dumb_create		= rockchip_gem_dumb_create,
 	.gem_prime_import_sg_table	= rockchip_gem_prime_import_sg_table,
 	DRM_FBDEV_DMA_DRIVER_OPS,
